description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and experienced paediatric physiotherapist with knowledge and skills in a broad range of paediatric conditions to lead and develop the service in the acute trust setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will involve a clinical outpatient caseload based at Wexham Park Hospital, supervision of the Band 6 and Band 5 physiotherapists, and management of the paediatric physiotherapy service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Areas of involvement include Children’s Ward, NNU, MDT clinics in cystic fibrosis, oncology and rheumatology, musculoskeletal outpatients, close links with the paediatricians, MDT and the paediatric community team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It will involve close liaison with relevant hospital consultants, local GPs and colleagues working within the local ICS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to take part in the weekend working and on call rota&#39;s and will have access to regular training and supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is full time but there may some flexibility around hours for a suitable candidate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chelsea Calvert - Physiotherapy In Patient Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;chelsea.calvert@nhs.net / 07747 012067&lt;/p&gt;
